SUMMARY:Bikes & Bats
DTSTAMP:20260620T143425Z
DTSTART:20260620T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Buffalo Bayou Partnership and BikeHouston for a batty good
	 time with a bike ride to the Waugh Bridge Bat Colony! \nBring your bike f
	or an evening ride along Buffalo Bayou to the Waugh Drive Bridge\, where y
	ou’ll witness an unforgettable sight—more than 300\,000 Mexican free-taile
	d bats emerging at sunset. Along the way\, bat expert DeAndra Ramsey will 
	share insights about these fascinating and important creatures—affectionat
	ely known as “sky puppies.” Spots are limited\, so reserve yours today! \n
	Cost\n$10 \nDuration\n2 hours / 3 miles \nMeeting Location\nThe Water Work
	s in Buffalo Bayou Park (105-B Sabine St) \nTICKETS\n\nhttps://buffalobayo
	u.org/event/2026-bikes-and-bats-2/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou Partnership
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-bikes-and-bats-2/
LOCATION:THE WATER WORKS\, 105 Sabine Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77007\, Unite
	d States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:buffalo-bayou-partnership
CATEGORIES:Buffalo Bayou Partnership
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
